From: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
Subject: [PATCH] pyproject: relax setuptools build-time pin

Upstream pins setuptools to ~=80.9.0 (>=80.9, <81), which is incompatible
with the setuptools shipped by OE (82.x). Drop the upper bound so the
build accepts whatever the host has staged.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [OE-specific]

---
 pyproject.toml | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/pyproject.toml b/pyproject.toml
--- a/pyproject.toml
+++ b/pyproject.toml
@@ -34,7 +34,7 @@ requires = [
     # We build against the most recent supported NumPy 2.0 release;
     # see https://github.com/numpy/numpy/issues/27265
     "numpy~=2.0",
-    "setuptools~=80.9.0",
+    "setuptools>=80.9.0",
 ]
 build-backend = "setuptools.build_meta"

